faq who regulates the gambling industry in the uk the gambling commission is the official governmental body responsible for the regulation monitoring and supervision of all forms of gambling in the united kingdom including landbased and online casinos bingo operations sports betting and gaming machines the commission enforces the gambling act 2005 issues or revokes operating licences and various codes of practice and specifies the general license conditions operators are required to meet which are the most popular banking methods in the uk online casino players in the united kingdom can safely and easily make casino deposits and withdraw their winnings via a wide range of bank cards and other payment services popular banking methods include internationally accepted cards such as mastercard and visa ewallets like paypal skrill and neteller as well as prepaid services such as paysafecard ecopayz and entropay casino players can also use various online banking methods direct bank transfers and cheques do i need to register an account to play casino games yes ukbased players are required to sign up for a user account if they want to play games in an online casino since may 2019 when new age and identity verification rules took effect players must provide proof that they are of legal age to take part in gambling activities the new age restrictions also apply to freetoplay gambling products is it safe to play casino games online it is perfectly safe to play realmoney games in online casinos which are licensed and regulated in the uk licensed operators comply with the strict rules and regulations in the country associated with fairness responsible gambling and overall online security all casino websites use modern encryption technologies to protect sensitive user data and any financial transactions carried out online where can i seek help for my gambling problem gambling should be considered a recreational activity and if you recognize that you have a gambling problem you should seek professional help the national problem gambling clinic a specialist nhs clinic is available to individuals who live in england or wales the charitable company gamcare offers free information support and counselling for problem gamblers in the uk on the national gambling helpline 0808 8020 133 local support groups can be found in the gamblers anonymous uk
